31/08/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- British Ambassador to BiH Mathew Rycroft met with Republika Srpska (RS) President Dragan Cavic and Prime Minister Milorad Dodik in Banja Luka on Wednesday (30 August), to discuss key police reforms and planned constitutional changes in light of BiH's EU integration bid. 
They also discussed the 1 October parliamentary elections, with Rycroft urging all politicians to refrain from campaign rhetoric.
On Thursday, Dodik kicked off an official visit to Serbia. 
He plans talks with counterpart Vojislav Kostunica, President Boris Tadic and Finance Minister Mladjan Dinkic. 
(RTRS, PBS, Fena - 30/08/06)
